experiment_title: Illumina HiSeq 4000 sequencing: RNA-Seq of Streptomyces venezuelae to compare global gene expression between the wild-type and BldB deletion strains after 10, 14 and 22 hours of growth.
study_title: RNA-Seq of Streptomyces venezuelae to compare global gene expression between the wild-type and BldB deletion strains after 10, 14 and 22 hours of growth.
sample_description: Protocols: Mycelial mass was harvested by centrifugation for 30 ml cultures grown overnight (14 hours). Streptomyces venezuelae NRRL B-65442 (Wild-type and BldB deletion strain both were grown in triplicates for in 30 ml shaken cultures at 30 degrees Celsius in the Maltose-Yeast extract-Malt Extract (MYM) medium supplemented with R2 trace element solution. The .bam files produced by aligning the reads to the genome were used as input to the featureCounts tool of the Bioconductor package Rsubread (version 2.0.0) along with a a .saf file containing coordinates of genes in the genome. This produced a table of counts of reads mapping to every gene in the genome. Mycelial pellets were washed with 1x PBS followed by lysis and RNA purification using the RNEasy kit (Quiagen). Purified RNA samples were treated with on-column DNase I (Qiagen), followed by an additional DNase I treatment (Turbo DNA-free, Invitrogen). rRNA depletion and Library construction were carried out by Genewiz (NJ, USA).

experiment_title: Illumina NovaSeq 6000 sequencing: Global transcript levels during growth of Streptomyces venezuelae wild-type strain
study_title: Global transcript levels during growth of Streptomyces venezuelae wild-type strain
sample_description: Protocols: RNA was isolated from Streptomyces venezeulae wild-type strain cultivated in 5 mL MYM liquid medium for 10, 15, or 20 hours (each time point in triplicate). Mycelia were collected by centrifugation, frozen, and stored at -70C for subsequent RNA isolation. RNA from mycelia was isolated using the GeneJET RNA isolation kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific, US). The lysozyme concentration in the suspension buffer was increased to up to 10 mg/mL to improve the yield of mycelium lysis. The isolated RNA was digested with TURBO DNase I (Invitrogen, United States) and subsequently, purified and concentrated using a GeneJET RNA Cleanup kit (Thermo Fischer Scientific, US) RNA libraries were prepared for sequencing using standard Illumina protocols (NEBNext Ultra II Directional RNA Library Prep Kit). rRNA was removed using Ribo-Zero Ribosoma RNA Removal Kit (Illumina)

experiment_title: Illumina HiSeq 4000 paired end sequencing: Differential gene expression analysis by RNA-Seq for the bldC deletion strain and the wild type of Streptomyces venezuelae strain NRRL B-65442 after 10 and 14 hours of culture
study_title: Differential gene expression analysis by RNA-Seq for the bldC deletion strain and the wild type of Streptomyces venezuelae strain NRRL B-65442 after 10 and 14 hours of culture
sample_description: Protocols: Streptomyces venezuelae strain NRRL B-65442 (NCBI Ref: NZ_CP018074.1) was used as the wild type strain. The BldC deletion strain (SV25) was made using Redirect PCR targeting (Gust et al., 2003 Gust et al., 2004), to replace the bldC gene with a single apramycin resistance (apr) cassette in the wild type Streptomyces venezuelae strain. Cultures were grown in 4 x 30 ml volumes of MYM-TAP according to Stuttard C. 1982. (Microbiology 128:115121) made with 50% tap water and supplemented with 200 ul of trace element solution (Kieser T et al. 2000. Practical Streptomyces genetics. John Innes Foundation, Norwich, United Kingdom.) per 100 ml. Cultures were incubated at 30 degrees c and 250 RPM until sporulation was at an advanced stage (38 hours, as determined by light microscopy). Mycelial pellets from duplicate MYM cultures were washed in PBS and resuspended in 900 l lysis solution (400 l phenol [pH4.3], 100 l chlorophorm:isoamyl alcohol (24:1) and 400 l RLT buffer [Qiagen]) with lysing matrix B (MP Biomedicals) and homogenised using a FastPrep FP120 Cell Disruptor (Thermo Savant). Two pulses of 30 seconds of intensity 6.0 were applied with cooling down for 1 min on ice between pulses. Supernatants were centrifuged for 15 min, full-speed on a bench-top centrifuge at 4C and then treated according to the instructions given in the RNEasy Kit (Qiagen). The RNA samples were treated with on-column DNase I (Qiagen), followed by an additional DNase I treatment (Turbo DNA-free, Ambion) until they were free of DNA contamination (determined by PCR amplification of hrdB). Library preparation was performed by the sequencing contractor Genewiz (NJ, USA).

(Microbiology 128:115121) made with 50% tap water and supplemented with 200 ul of trace element solution (Kieser T et al. 2000. Practical Streptomyces genetics. John Innes Foundation, Norwich, United Kingdom.) per 100 ml. Cultures were incubated at 30 degrees c and 250 RPM until sporulation was at an advanced stage (38 hours, as determined by light microscopy). Mycelial pellets from duplicate MYM cultures were washed in PBS and resuspended in 900 l lysis solution (400 l phenol [pH4.3], 100 l chlorophorm:isoamyl alcohol (24:1) and 400 l RLT buffer [Qiagen]) with lysing matrix B (MP Biomedicals) and homogenised using a FastPrep FP120 Cell Disruptor (Thermo Savant). Two pulses of 30 seconds of intensity 6.0 were applied with cooling down for 1 min on ice between pulses. Supernatants were centrifuged for 15 min, full-speed on a bench-top centrifuge at 4C and then treated according to the instructions given in the RNEasy Kit (Qiagen). The RNA samples were treated with on-column DNase I (Qiagen), followed by an additional DNase I treatment (Turbo DNA-free, Ambion) until they were free of DNA contamination (determined by PCR amplification of hrdB). Library preparation was performed by the sequencing contractor Genewiz (NJ, USA).

experiment_title: Illumina NovaSeq 6000 sequencing: RNA-Seq of Streptomyces venezuelae grown overnight (14 hrs) with Mitomycin-C against untreated controls.
study_title: RNA-Seq of Streptomyces venezuelae grown overnight (14 hrs) with Mitomycin-C against untreated controls.
sample_description: Protocols: Mycelial mass was harvested by centrifugation for 30 ml cultures grown overnight (14 hours). Streptomyces venezuelae NRRL B-65442 was grown in triplicates for 17 hours in 30 ml shaken cultures at 30 degrees Celsius in the Maltose-Yeast extract-Malt Extract (MYM) medium supplemented with R2 trace element solution containing 0.25 ug/ml Mitomycin C (MMC). Controls were also grown similarly in triplicates except that the medium did not contain any MMC. Mitomycin C was added to the growth medium at 2.5 ug per ml. The .bam files produced by aligning the reads to the genome were used as input to the featureCounts tool of the Bioconductor package Rsubread (version 2.0.0) along with a a .saf file containing coordinates of genes in the genome. This produced a table of counts of reads mapping to every gene in the genome. Mycelial pellets were washed with 1x PBS followed by lysis and RNA purification using the RNEasy kit (Quiagen). Purified RNA samples were treated with on-column DNase I (Qiagen), followed by an additional DNase I treatment (Turbo DNA-free, Invitrogen). rRNA depletion and Library construction were carried out by Genewiz (NJ, USA).
